    <text id="B0210T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McDonnell writes Jackson concerning his accounts of clothing distributed by the
                    Bureau.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R. F. &amp; A.
                        L.</abbr><lb/>Head <abbr expan="Quarters">Qrs</abbr> 9<hi rend="super">t</hi>
                    Sub <abbr expan="District">Dist.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient">Mr. <abbr expan="Thomas">Thos.</abbr> P.
                            Jackson<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner">Asst Sub
                            Asst Comr</abbr><lb/>Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-03-04"><abbr expan="March">Mch</abbr> 4/68</date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Your communication <abbr expan="Number">No</abbr> 10. <unclear>2d.V.68.</unclear>
                    <abbr expan="March">Mch</abbr> 2d 1868, reporting the issue of the remainder of
                    the clothing in your hands has been received.</p>

                <p>All clothing charged to you has been properly accounted for except one Shirt, on
                    assuming charge at Staunton, you sent to this office a <unclear>memo</unclear>
                    receipt of property transfered to you by Mr. Tukey, among the rest 45 shirts,
                    That receipt is now in this office. Since then 100 more were acknowledged by you
                    to have been received, of these 144 have been reported by you as issued, as
                    stated in your letter 2d inst., above referred to.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="Obedient">Obed.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Servant">Svt</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>John A. McDonnell<lb/>Sub <abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst
                        Comr</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
